'''皮埃尔·勒内·德利涅子爵'''（{{lang-fr|Vicomte Pierre René Deligne}}，{{lang-en|Pierre Deligne}}，{{bd|1944年|10月3日}}），[[比利时|比利时]][[代数几何|代数几何]][[学者|学者]]，20世纪中后期最知名的[[数学家|数学家]]之一。他最重要的贡献之一是20世纪70年代关于{{link-en|韦伊猜想|Weil conjectures}}的工作。他也是大数学家[[亚历山大·格罗滕迪克|亚历山大·格罗滕迪克]]的得意门生之一。

== 生平 ==
德利涅生于[[布鲁塞尔|布鲁塞尔]]，自幼数学天赋出众，初中时就在老师建议下开始阅读[[布尔巴基|布尔巴基]]小组写的专著《集合论》，高中时就已经获得机会进入前沿数学家的讨论班。他就读于[[布鲁塞尔自由大学|布鲁塞尔自由大学]]，曾受知名数学家[[雅克·蒂茨|雅克·蒂茨]]栽培，后来又被带到布尔巴基学派的讨论班上和[[亚历山大·格罗滕迪克|亚历山大·格罗滕迪克]]等其他重要数学家见面。他回忆第一次见到格罗腾迪克时，觉得对方高个子、大光头的形象有点怪异<ref>见{{harvnb|Raussen|2013|p=17-19}}，摘录如下：“He was a little strange, with his shaved head, a very tall man.”</ref>。已是大数学家的格罗滕迪克对当时还是新人的德利涅所问的问题给与了耐心的解释，这让德利涅觉得格罗滕迪克非常有亲和力<ref>见{{harvnb|Raussen|2013|p=17-19}}，摘录如下：“I think that many other mathematicians would have thought that if you didn't know the answer, there wouldn’t be any point to speak to you. This was not his reaction at all. Very patiently he told me that... He was very open to people who were ignorant. I think that you should not ask him the same stupid question three times, but twice was all right.”</ref>。

1968年他在[[格罗滕迪克|格罗滕迪克]]指导下完成[[博士|博士]]论文。1970年26岁的德利涅成为[[法國高等科學研究所|法國高等科學研究所]]教授。他在那里完成了关于[[霍奇理论|霍奇理论]]和{{link-en|韦伊猜想|Weil conjectures}}的工作。格罗滕迪克很有信心按照自己提供的一套思路框架来逐步解决韦伊猜想，并借此证明其数学思想的威力，但是德利涅却另辟蹊径搞定了韦伊猜想。德利涅虽凭借这一成绩获得了[[菲尔兹奖|菲尔兹奖]]，但是他也承认老师格罗滕迪克对此事并不满意<ref>见{{harvnb|Raussen|2013|p=17-19}}，摘录如下：“I used a completely different idea. It is inspired by the work of Rankin and his work on automorphic forms. It still has a number of applications, but it did not realize the dream of Grothendieck. ... It would have been much nicer if his program had been realized. He did not think that there would be another way to do it. When he heard I had proved it, he felt I must have done this and that, which I hadn't. I think that’s the reason for the disappointment.”</ref>。格罗滕迪克的老搭档[[让-皮埃尔·塞尔|让-皮埃尔·塞尔]]则觉得韦伊猜想被解决是一件值得开心的事情<ref>见{{harvnb|Raussen|2013|p=17-19}}。</ref>。

1984年，德利涅移居美国，进入[[普林斯顿高等研究院|普林斯顿高等研究院]]。在普林斯顿的生活同样充满挑战，这里的讨论会经常是数学家和物理学家共同参加的，他也在这里遇见了[[爱德华·威滕|爱德华·威滕]]这样的提问既有意思、又能把自己难倒的顶尖物理学家<ref>见{{harvnb|Raussen|2013|p=20-22}}，摘录如下：“In both places there are physicists, but I think the contact with them was more fruitful for me in Princeton than it was in Bures. In Princeton, there have been common seminars. One year was very intense, with both mathematicians and physicists participating. This was due mainly to the presence of Edward Witten. He has received the Fields Medal even though he is a physicist. When Witten asks me questions, it's always very interesting to try to answer them, but it can be frustrating as well.”</ref>。普林斯顿开展的学科研究和会议也更为广泛，他也会忙里抽闲去听中国古代历史之类的人文及社会类学科的报告会<ref>见{{harvnb|Raussen|2013|p=20-22}}，摘录如下：“Princeton is also bigger in the sense that it has not only maths and physics, but also the School of Historical Studies and the School of Social Sciences. There is no real scientific interaction with these Schools but it is pleasant to be able to go and hear a lecture about, for instance, ancient China.”</ref>。

2013年，德利涅在[[阿贝尔奖|阿贝尔奖]]得奖采访中表示自己觉得导师的{{link-en|动机 (代数几何)|Motive (algebraic geometry)|动机理论}}在今后10年内看不到有明显进展的迹象，但自己也做好了被打脸的准备<ref>见{{harvnb|Raussen|2013|p=22}}，摘录如下：“Whether or not it's within reach in ten years, I have absolutely no idea; as it should be… but I would very much like to see progress in our understanding of motives. Which path to take and what are the correct questions, is very much in the air. Grothendieck's program relied on proving the existence of algebraic cycles with some properties. To me this looks hopeless, but I may be wrong.”</ref>。

== 数学观 ==
德利涅认为研究数学应该更关注新工具的创造和对学科大图景的理解。他的导师格罗滕迪克曾对他说过数学绝不是一种竞赛式的活动。<ref>见{{harvnb|Raussen|2013|p=21}}，摘录如下：“For Grothendieck it was very clear: he once told me that mathematics is not a competition sport. Mathematicians are different and some will want to be the first, especially if they are working on very specific and difficult questions. For me it's more important to create tools and to understand the general picture.”</ref>

